books.title: The Lord of the Rings
books.author: J.R.R. Tolkien
books.synopsis: A epic fantasy adventure following Frodo Baggins and the Fellowship as they journey to destroy the One Ring and defeat the Dark Lord Sauron.

books.title: A Game of Thrones
books.author: George R.R. Martin
books.synopsis: The first book in A Song of Ice and Fire series, set in the fictional Seven Kingdoms of Westeros, where summers span decades and winters can last a lifetime.

books.title: Dune
books.author: Frank Herbert
books.synopsis: Set in the distant future amidst a feudal interstellar society, Dune tells the story of young Paul Atreides as he and his family accept control of the desert planet Arrakis.

books.title: The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy
books.author: Douglas Adams
books.synopsis: A comedic science fiction series following the misadventures of Arthur Dent after Earth is demolished to make way for a galactic freeway.

books.author: George Orwell
books.synopsis: A dystopian social science fiction novel about Winston Smith, a low-ranking member of 'the Party' in London, in the nation of Oceania, where the Party exercises total control.

books.title: To Kill a Mockingbird
books.author: Harper Lee
books.synopsis: A novel about the serious issues of rape and racial inequality told through the eyes of a young girl in the American South during the 1930s.

books.title: The Catcher in the Rye
books.author: J.D. Salinger
books.synopsis: The story of Holden Caulfield, a teenager from New York City who is expelled from his prep school and then takes a journey around his hometown.

books.title: The Hobbit
books.author: J.R.R. Tolkien
books.synopsis: The story of Bilbo Baggins, a hobbit who enjoys a comfortable, unambitious life until he is swept away on an epic adventure by the wizard Gandalf and thirteen dwarves.

books.title: Project Hail Mary
books.author: Andy Weir
books.synopsis: A lone astronaut must save the earth when he wakes up on a space station with no memory of how he got there.

books.title: The Seven Husbands of Evelyn Hugo
books.author: Taylor Jenkins Reid
books.synopsis: Reclusive Hollywood icon Evelyn Hugo finally decides to tell her life story to unknown journalist Monique Grant.
